  "prompt": "Why do I have to tip the server?",
  "response": "Tipping servers in restaurants and other service industries is a customary practice that serves several purposes:\n\n1. **Compensation**: In many places, especially in the United States, servers often earn a base wage that is lower than the minimum wage because they rely on tips to make up the difference. Tipping helps ensure they receive a livable income.\n\n2. **Incentive for Good Service**: Tipping acts as an incentive for servers to provide good service. The prospect of receiving a larger tip can motivate servers to be attentive, friendly, and efficient in their work.\n\n3. **Cultural Norm**: In many cultures, tipping is expected and considered a way to show appreciation for good service. It's seen as part of social etiquette, and not tipping can be viewed as rude or disrespectful.\n\n4. **Support for the Service Industry**: Tipping helps support workers in the service industry, many of whom may work irregular hours or face job instability. It enables them to earn more based on their performance and the satisfaction of customers.\n\n5. **Customer Experience**: A gratuity often reflects the dining experience, rewarding servers who go above and beyond to enhance the meal for patrons.\n\nWhile tipping practices can vary significantly from one country to another, and some places have different expectations regarding service charges included in the bill, it\u2019s generally a good idea to familiarize yourself with the local customs when dining out.",
